File: PSL Chairperson Irvin Khoza. JOHANNESBURG - Premier Soccer League Chairperson Irvin Khoza announced the PSL will suspend all football fixtures this week until further notice. Khoza made the announcement during a media briefing on Monday at the PSL headquarters. South Africa has closed the majority of its border posts following an increase in infections in the country. President Cyril Ramaphosa announced control measures for the viral outbreak on Sunday evening. Scientists say a vaccine for COVID-19 could only be available in over a year. 